---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" href="/povwhite.png" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<title>About | Piling Obrang Vidyo</title>
	</head>
	<body class="bg-black text-white font-stack max-w-360 mx-auto">
		<Navbar />
		<div class="m-6 flex flex-col gap-8">
			<section class="flex flex-col gap-4">
				<h1 class="text-2xl">About</h1>
				<div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 w-full">
					<img
						src="/img/grouppic.png"
						class="rounded-lg aspect-video object-cover"
					/>
					<img
						src="/img/pov2.JPG"
						class="rounded-lg aspect-video object-cover"
					/>
				</div>
				<p>
					Since 2004, Piling Obrang Vidyo (POV) has been a space for a lot of
					student filmmakers to create their mark - have their voice heard and a
					chance to exhibit their short films on the big screen. Since then, POV
					has become a platform to empower the stories of the Filipino youth.
					<br /><br />In its 22nd year, POV XXXII remains resonant and vivid
					with the theme <b>Kalampag ng Kulay</b>. This edition positions cinema
					as a space of disruption, one that refuses to be silent and asserts on
					being felt. Rooted in youth perspectives and emerging voices, the
					festival highlights how student filmmaking challenges conventions and
					pushes the boundaries of storytelling. <b>Kulay</b> affirms the many forms
					cinema can take, celebrating expression, emotion, and the hues of visual
					storytelling. <b>Kalampag</b> speaks to cinema’s loudness and its power
					to unsettle and disrupt. Together, when sound and image collide, they create
					an impact that shakes the world within and beyond the screen.
					<br /><br />This year, POV will also hold <b>PeliKolektibo</b>, a
					program for budding high school film critics of any medium where they
					get to undergo a series of workshops, consultations, and critique
					sessions.<br /><br />In a time when colors of truth are being bleached
					from the public, when the machinery of power works to mute every
					dissenting hue into a uniform and obedient grey, filmmakers do not
					have the luxury of neutrality. Filmmakers are here to stain, to bleed
					color into every crack of a world that demands their silence. Kalampag
					ng Kulay is a provocation. It is the insistence that cinema must be
					loud, must be chromatic in its rage, must refuse the comfortable
					greyness of complicity.
				</p>
				<div>
					<h1 class="text-2xl">The Team</h1>
				</div>

				<div class="flex flex-wrap gap-8 md:gap-24 justify-center">
					{
						teamRoles.map((team) => (
							<div class="flex flex-col items-center w-fit gap-1">
								<div class="flex gap-3">
									{team.members.map((member) => (
										<div class="flex flex-col items-center w-full max-w-64 gap-2">
											<img
												src={member.img}
												class="aspect-square object-cover rounded-lg"
												alt={member.name}
											/>

											<span class="text-center text-lg">{member.name}</span>
										</div>
									))}
								</div>
								<div class="w-full h-[2px] bg-white" />
								<div class="flex flex-col items-center">
									<span class="text-sm">{team.role}</span>
								</div>
							</div>
						))
					}
				</div>
			</section>
			<Footer />
		</div>
	</body>
</html>
